1 Section 1. Chapter 449A of NRS is hereby amended by
2 adding thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 to 8, inclusive,
3 of this act.
4 Sec. 2. Sections 2 to 8, inclusive, of this act may be cited as
5 the Right to Reproductive Health Care Act.
6 Sec. 3. As used in sections 2 to 8, inclusive, of this act, unless
7 the context otherwise requires, the words and terms defined in
8 sections 4, 5 and 6 of this act have the meanings ascribed to them
9 in those sections.
10 Sec. 4. “Governmental entity” means the State of Nevada or
11 any of its agencies or political subdivisions.
12 Sec. 5. “Provider of health care” has the meaning ascribed
13 to it in NRS 629.031.
14 Sec. 6. “Reproductive health care” means medical, surgical,
15 counseling or referral services relating to the human reproductive
16 system, including, without limitation, services relating to
17 pregnancy, contraception, miscarriage, in vitro fertilization or any
18 procedure or care found by a competent medical professional to be
19 appropriate based upon the wishes of a patient and in accordance
20 with the laws of this State.
21 Sec. 7. 1. Except as otherwise provided in this section, the
22 provisions of sections 2 to 8, inclusive, of this act apply to all state
23 and local laws and ordinances and the implementation of those
24 laws and ordinances, whether statutory or otherwise, and whether
25 enacted before, on or after January 1, 2026. The provisions of
26 sections 2 to 8, inclusive, of this act do not apply to NRS 442.250
27 or the implementation of NRS 442.250.
28 2. State laws that are enacted on or after January 1, 2026, are
29 subject to the provisions of sections 2 to 8, inclusive, of this act
30 unless the law explicitly excludes such application by reference to
31 this section.
32 3. The provisions of sections 2 to 8, inclusive, of this act do
33 not:
34 (a) Authorize a governmental entity to burden:
