11 Sec. 8. 1. Except as otherwise provided in this section, a
12 governmental entity shall not enact or implement any limitation or
13 requirement that:
14 (a) Expressly, effectively, implicitly or, as implemented, singles
15 out reproductive health care, drugs or devices related to
16 reproductive health care or information related to reproductive
17 health care or any providers of health care or facilities that
18 provide reproductive health care, drugs or devices related to
19 reproductive health care or information related to reproductive
20 health care; and
21 (b) Substantially burdens:
22 (1) The access of a person to reproductive health care,
23 drugs or devices related to reproductive health care or information
24 related to reproductive health care; or
25 (2) The ability of a provider of health care to provide
26 reproductive health care, drugs or devices related to reproductive
27 health care or information related to reproductive health care
28 within the scope of practice, training and experience of the
29 provider of health care.
30 2. A governmental entity may enact a requirement or
31 limitation described in subsection 1 if the governmental entity
32 demonstrates by clear and convincing evidence that the burden
33 imposed by the requirement or limitation on the activity described
34 in paragraph (b) of subsection 1, as applied to the person or
35 provider of health care who is subject to the burden:
36 (a) Furthers a compelling interest; and
37 (b) Is the least restrictive means of furthering that interest.
38 3. Notwithstanding any provision of NRS 41.0305 to 41.039,
39 inclusive, but subject to the limitation on damages set forth in
40 NRS 41.035 when applicable, a person or provider of health care
41 who has been substantially burdened in violation of this section
42 may assert that violation as a claim or defense in a judicial
43 proceeding and obtain appropriate relief. A court shall award
44 costs and attorney’s fees to a person who prevails on such a claim
45 or defense pursuant to this section.
